CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 11, 1953, pg. 21 reads: "Bunny Queen - Second Lieut. Helen Walker crowns First Lieut. Ellen Johnson of the Sport Unit of Mosiwidael Temple 38, IBPOE of W, at the Easter affair held at the North Side Elks Home last Friday night. "Bunny Queen" Ellen Johnson won a round trip ticket to Rochester, N.Y., while her aide, Helen Walker, won a one-way ticket to the same city.  Maj. Mabel Terry was chairman of the event, Past Capt. Bertie Coley, co-chairman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Four young women, including Ellen Johnson seated in center wearing light colored gown with ruched halter top and beaded design on straps, being crowned by Helen Walker wearing eyeglasses and satin short sleeve gown, gathered in North Side Elks with leaf patterned carpet and striped curtains
